      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To optimize the function to handle large values of `n` efficiently, let’s reduce the time complexity. We can use mathematical properties to avoid the nested loops. The summation in your code can actually be simplified to a mathematical formula which only requires an operation linear in time `O(n)`.\n\nYou need to find the summation of `(i * j)` from `i` to `n-1` and `j` to `i`.\n\nHere's an optimized version:\n\n```python\ndef solve_sequence(n):\n    result = 0\n    for i in range(n):\n        result += (i * sum(range(i + 1))) // 123\n    return result\n```\n\nThis version will run in linear time `O(n)` instead of `O(n^2)`, drastically reducing computation time even for large `n` like 10^7.",
